# Blossom Assistant (extension)

Client for ChatRouter at `http://127.0.0.1:8081`. Local-first coding.

## Ownership (do not invert)

- **Extension:** editor attach, repo knowledge, disk checks (`fs.access`), Apply / auto-apply / auto-save, fence→file mapping, UI summary.
- **ChatRouter:** routing (persona/coder/cloud), RAG, coding_rules, GGUF hot-swap.
- ChatRouter cannot see the project disk unless the extension puts facts in the prompt. **Disk truth = extension.**

## Critical rules

- **CREATE vs EDIT:** new files get their own fence (`path=contacts.html`); never dump a new page into attached `index.html`.
- Multi-file = multiple path-labeled fences (or `**file.ext**` heading above fence). Apply must create all of them.
- Parse path from: `path=…`, bold/heading above fence, HTML comments — **never** invent paths from `<title>` (caused `validhtmlexample.html`).
- Auto-apply + auto-save must land on disk without Ctrl+S.
- After coding: Summary card with model notes + backend (Local coder / Claude / Gemini). No "Done — applied…" spam.
- Link / unused-file asks:
  - Inject `[LINK CHECK]` with EXISTS/MISSING from real `fs.access`.
  - Never remove EXISTS links.
  - "Delete unused / safe to delete" = extension proposes `kind: delete` for `[UNUSED FILES]` and Apply/Auto-apply unlinks (model fences ignored in that mode).
  - Explicit `DELETE path=file.ext` / ```delete path=…``` also become delete Apply cards.
  - Inject clear `[TASK BRIEF]` so the model does not confuse orphans with dead links.

## Key files

- `src/agent/editorContext.ts` — LINK CHECK, UNUSED FILES, task brief
- `src/agent/applyFromResponse.ts` — fence→Apply
- `src/agent/orchestrator.ts` — turn pipeline
- `src/agent/tools.ts` — apply + save
- `src/chat/ChatPanel.ts` — UI

Backend rules: `Documents/Blossom/PythonScripts/` — coordinate; do not duplicate disk I/O there.

## When changing the plugin

Prefer verified context injection over hoping the local coder "knows." Language-agnostic path fences + disk checks; HTML href/orphan helpers are OK as specialized cases. After changes: `npm run compile`, reload, test create+edit, link-check with existing siblings, unused delete candidate, auto-apply saves.
